OL,3,CYounger workers more likely to suffer
OL,4,Cburnout as generation gap grows `
OL,5,Csurvey
OL,7,FThe proportion of younger workers
OL,8,Fneeding time off for stress has grown
OL,9,Fcompared with older colleagues,
OL,10,Faccording to a report on burnout which
OL,11,Falso revealed far fewer feel
OL,12,Fcomfortable opening up to bosses about
OL,13,Fthe pressure they are under.
OL,15,FWhile around one in 10 workers aged 45
OL,16,Fand above needed time off last year
OL,17,Fbecause of poor mental health caused
OL,18,Fby stress, it was around one in three
OL,19,Ffor those aged 18-24, Mental Health UK
OL,20,Fsaid.
