OL,3,CYounger workers more likely to suffer
OL,4,Cburnout as generation gap grows `
OL,5,Csurvey
OL,7,FThe charity's second annual Burnout
OL,8,FReport found this was the case for
OL,9,Faround 29% of workers aged 25-34 last
OL,10,Fyear, up from 23% the previous year;
OL,11,Fand a quarter (25%) of 35 to 44-year-
OL,12,Folds, up from a fifth in 2023.
OL,14,FAmong 18 to 24-year-olds the
OL,15,Fproportion saw a smaller rise, from
OL,16,F34% to 35% last year.
