OL,3,CYounger workers more likely to suffer
OL,4,Cburnout as generation gap grows `
OL,5,Csurvey
OL,7,FYounger workers were most likely to
OL,8,Ffeel stressed because of having to
OL,9,Fregularly work unpaid overtime (48% of
OL,10,F18 to 24-year-olds), and taking on
OL,11,Fextra hours to deal with the increased
OL,12,Fcost of living (46%).
OL,14,FWorkers aged 25-34 reported high
OL,15,Fstress caused by a high or increased
OL,16,Fworkload (56%) and fears of redundancy
OL,17,For around job security (45%).
